81.6	Metal_Gear_Solid	Metal Gear Solid	Metal Gear Solid Metaru Gia Soriddo, commonly abbreviated as MGS) is a video game by Hideo Kojima. The game was developed by Konami Computer Entertainment Japan and first published by Konami in 1998 for the PlayStation video game console. It is the sequel to Kojimas early MSX2 computer games Metal Gear and Metal Gear 2: Solid Snake. The game featured cinematic cutscenes rendered using the in-game engine and graphics, as well as voice acting in numerous codec sequences.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/3/33/Metal_Gear_Solid_cover_art.png/252px-Metal_Gear_Solid_cover_art.png
